1
00:00:00,041 --> 00:00:00,041
25.000

2
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:27,652
Yoseph Shiloach

3
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:30,655
Yona Elian

4
00:00:30,822 --> 00:00:33,658
Muhammad Bakri

5
00:01:00,685 --> 00:01:10,820
Desperado Square

6
00:02:13,717 --> 00:02:18,471
Editor:
Yoseph Greenfeld

7
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:22,559
What's the matter with Yisrael?
He overslept.

8
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:26,438
I don't know, he always wakes
the neighborhood up on time.

9
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:40,326
Photography:
Dror Moreh

10
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:04,434
Pull!

11
00:03:04,934 --> 00:03:06,811
Pull.
- Be careful not to fall.

12
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:08,646
Don't worry,
Baruch.

13
00:03:13,401 --> 00:03:16,488
Yisrael the Indian is arriving.
- He's late today.

14
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:18,615
Yisrael,
you asshole!

15
00:03:18,782 --> 00:03:20,075
You're 10 minutes late.

16
00:03:22,077 --> 00:03:23,453
I should be the alarm clock...

17
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:25,288
You? You'll have us
sleeping till noon.

18
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:27,040
No way.
I'm precise as a Swiss watch.

19
00:03:27,624 --> 00:03:28,750
Yeah, sure...

20
00:03:28,917 --> 00:03:32,629
Come down already.
It's getting hot here.

21
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:39,469
Producers:
Amir Harel & Haim Manor

22
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:56,027
All together now...

23
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:59,364
Director:
Benni Torati

24
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:04,494
It weighs a ton...

25
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:14,879
Did you speak to the synagogue
about the memorial service?

26
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:17,465
Everything's arranged, Mom.

27
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:21,094
How about the notices?

28
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:25,098
Yisrael plastered notices
all over the neighborhood.

29
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:50,165
Nissim.

30
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:52,167
Nissim!

31
00:04:56,338 --> 00:04:58,882
I had a dream about Dad,
blew my mind.

32
00:04:59,716 --> 00:05:03,428
I saw Dad standing
in front of the old theater.

33
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:07,849
You and Aaron were there too.

34
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:10,185
The whole neighborhood
was gathered around.

35
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:13,980
Dad was nailing the door
of the theater shut.

36
00:05:14,189 --> 00:05:16,066
Everyone was crying
like little children.

37
00:05:16,274 --> 00:05:18,485
Quite a dream.
- There's even more to it.

38
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:23,907
Then Dad tries to pry loose
the boards nailed to the door

39
00:05:24,074 --> 00:05:25,325
but he doesn't have the strength.

40
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:29,329
He grabs me by the collar,
like this... Like this.

41
00:05:29,496 --> 00:05:31,748
He asks me to help him.

42
00:05:31,873 --> 00:05:34,876
But my arms are weak
and the boards won't budge.

43
00:05:35,043 --> 00:05:38,088
Then Dad, with tears
in his eyes,

44
00:05:38,213 --> 00:05:40,757
makes me promise I'll do
one final screening

45
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:42,634
to undo the vow.

46
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:44,469
A vow is no laughing matter, Nissim.

47
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:47,639
I'll tell you his exact words:

48
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:51,309
"Screen one last movie
to undo the vow."

49
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:55,522
"Memorial service -
Morris Mandebon"

50
00:06:14,124 --> 00:06:15,625
How are you, Yisrael?

51
00:06:18,712 --> 00:06:19,921
Avram?

52
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:43,486
Seniora.

53
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:48,074
You won't believe it.
Avram is back.

54
00:06:49,034 --> 00:06:50,035
Avram? Which Avram?

55
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:54,122
Avram Mandebon. I just saw him
in the street, honest.

56
00:06:54,330 --> 00:06:58,043
Seniora, he hasn't changed.
He looks exactly the same.

57
00:06:58,960 --> 00:06:59,961
Yisrael.

58
00:07:01,755 --> 00:07:03,548
Which Avram? Dad's brother?

59
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:07,010
I swear, Nissim, I just saw him.
I wouldn't lie to you.

60
00:07:07,218 --> 00:07:08,553
What is he doing here?

61
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,388
He finally came to
his brother's memorial.

62
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:14,392
Enough.
- Why? Because he's an uncle?

63
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:19,939
Have a seat.
Want some coffee?

64
00:08:02,857 --> 00:08:04,442
I've dislocated my shoulder!

65
00:08:08,238 --> 00:08:11,783
One... two... three...

66
00:08:12,784 --> 00:08:14,661
It weighs a ton.

67
00:08:18,957 --> 00:08:20,500
Be careful!

68
00:08:21,084 --> 00:08:24,004
What happened?
- You got up late today...

69
00:08:24,129 --> 00:08:26,631
I'll play you a song
that'll set your hair on fire.

70
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:31,469
What's this?
- A mast for the bonfire.

71
00:08:32,095 --> 00:08:35,056
Tie a rag doll to the top
and it'll be a great bonfire.

72
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:38,351
Make the doll a Brezhinev.
- No. This year it's De-Gaulle.

73
00:08:42,397 --> 00:08:43,481
What?

74
00:08:43,732 --> 00:08:47,485
Lt'll look better if you
twist it around like this.

75
00:08:48,069 --> 00:08:49,487
You twist yours!

76
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:52,157
Do you owe me any money?
- I don't owe you anything.

77
00:08:52,282 --> 00:08:53,825
Just asking.

78
00:08:54,451 --> 00:08:55,660
Want to play again?

79
00:08:57,579 --> 00:08:58,830
Show me some money.

80
00:09:00,165 --> 00:09:01,458
Enough?

81
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:03,626
Pull up a crate.

82
00:09:12,594 --> 00:09:15,263
Both face cards lose,
the ace is the winner.

83
00:09:15,847 --> 00:09:17,515
Watch carefully.
Don't whine later.

84
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:25,523
Three cards: King here,
ace here, and queen here.

85
00:09:25,648 --> 00:09:27,901
King here, queen here,
and the ace here.

86
00:09:28,902 --> 00:09:30,904
Where's the ace?
- Morad, it's in the middle.

87
00:09:31,029 --> 00:09:32,739
It's in the middle.

88
00:09:33,073 --> 00:09:34,824
How do you flip a match?

89
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:37,994
Morad, do me a favor...
- Get lost!

90
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:45,710
Show me how to flip a match.
- Get lost, you Jellyfish!

91
00:09:50,507 --> 00:09:52,592
Both face cards lose,
the ace is the winner.

92
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:59,516
David, how are you, honey?

93
00:09:59,641 --> 00:10:01,267
Wait a second,
I want to talk to you.

94
00:10:01,476 --> 00:10:02,644
Wait a minute!

95
00:10:02,769 --> 00:10:04,729
Give me back my stockings,
you thief!

96
00:10:04,938 --> 00:10:06,940
Do you hear me, David?!

97
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:11,903
Sarah, go home.
Your food is getting cold.

98
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:18,702
Queen loses, king loses.
Where's the ace?

99
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:23,164
Queen.

100
00:10:26,209 --> 00:10:27,627
Let's play again.

101
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:29,212
He's broke.

102
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:31,673
Let him play for credit.
- I need a guarantee.

103
00:10:31,798 --> 00:10:33,967
Where can I get a guarantee?
- He hasn't got anything.

104
00:10:34,092 --> 00:10:36,261
He can wager the "mop".
- What?

105
00:10:36,386 --> 00:10:39,639
Wager the "mop".
- Over my dead body!

106
00:10:40,181 --> 00:10:41,808
Suit yourself.

107
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:42,934
Wait a minute, dumbo.

108
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:44,477
Morad, don't worry, he'll lose.

109
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:46,021
I can feel it this time.

110
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:53,403
Alright, the "mop"
against the entire pot.

111
00:10:55,530 --> 00:10:58,908
Winner takes all.
- Agreed.

112
00:10:59,034 --> 00:11:00,243
Sit down.

113
00:11:03,288 --> 00:11:05,040
Stay out of it.
This time I'm on my own.

114
00:11:05,165 --> 00:11:06,750
Morad, we'll hex him.

115
00:11:12,005 --> 00:11:14,632
No hexing!
- Oh, alright.

116
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:21,056
Both face cards lose,
the ace is the winner.

117
00:11:24,809 --> 00:11:26,102
Where's the ace?

118
00:11:29,356 --> 00:11:30,357
Are you sure?

119
00:11:30,607 --> 00:11:33,818
Up to your tricks again?
- No tricks.

120
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:37,197
You can still change your mind.
- This one.

121
00:11:39,991 --> 00:11:41,910
Damn!

122
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,377
Give me the "mop".

123
00:11:52,504 --> 00:11:54,547
Once he brings the money,
you give it back.

124
00:11:54,839 --> 00:11:56,132
Remember, you give it back.

125
00:11:56,257 --> 00:11:58,051
Bring the money,
get the "mop" back.

126
00:11:58,802 --> 00:12:01,888
If he doesn't return it,
we'll pluck out his eyebrows.

127
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:11,189
Take good care of it!

128
00:12:36,965 --> 00:12:39,384
Taking him for a joyride?
- Hi!

129
00:12:40,927 --> 00:12:42,971
Oh my goodness!
- What is it?

130
00:12:43,847 --> 00:12:46,266
What have you done to yourself?

131
00:12:46,850 --> 00:12:48,518
He looks good like this.

132
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:53,732
He lost the "mop" to Yisrael.

133
00:12:54,065 --> 00:12:56,192
He'll give it back to me
once I pay.

134
00:12:56,568 --> 00:12:57,902
Sure.

135
00:12:58,695 --> 00:13:01,406
So, planning to set
the neighborhood on fire?

136
00:13:01,531 --> 00:13:04,075
The bonfire they put up
in the Ezra quarter

137
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:06,703
is nothing compared to ours.

138
00:13:06,828 --> 00:13:09,831
It wasn't the real thing.
They only had tires to burn.

139
00:13:09,956 --> 00:13:11,708
We'll use wood.

140
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:14,377
Isn't this a tire?
- No, it's for sitting on.

141
00:13:14,669 --> 00:13:17,922
Will there be hot potatoes?
- Charcoal, more likely.

142
00:13:19,591 --> 00:13:20,592
Who's that yelling?

143
00:13:24,846 --> 00:13:27,307
Climb aboard.
Let's get moving.

144
00:13:28,475 --> 00:13:30,185
Step on it, Baruch!

145
00:13:30,477 --> 00:13:33,146
Don't take my gas canisters!
- I'll bring them back.

146
00:13:33,271 --> 00:13:35,899
No, don't take them!
- I'll bring them back!

147
00:13:36,691 --> 00:13:40,195
What's going on?
- Nothing. Clear the area.

148
00:13:40,362 --> 00:13:41,780
He's taking my canisters.

149
00:13:41,905 --> 00:13:43,740
I told you,
I'll bring them back.

150
00:13:44,699 --> 00:13:46,868
Mrs. Leah, please step aside.

151
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:49,829
Now put them back
and beat it.

152
00:13:49,954 --> 00:13:51,623
And don't raise any dust.

153
00:13:52,624 --> 00:13:55,168
Do you think you're
the law around here?

154
00:13:55,293 --> 00:13:57,754
It's between me and her,
so keep out of it!

155
00:13:57,921 --> 00:14:00,215
Beat it before I spatter you
all over the place.

156
00:14:07,597 --> 00:14:09,140
Enough, Nissim.

157
00:14:10,016 --> 00:14:11,893
If I see you here again

158
00:14:12,018 --> 00:14:13,853
I'll chop off your legs.

159
00:14:15,939 --> 00:14:17,190
Get lost.

160
00:14:27,325 --> 00:14:30,120
Mrs. Leah, don't worry,
we'll put back the canisters.

161
00:14:30,286 --> 00:14:33,540
Bless you. He keeps
stealing them all the time.

162
00:14:33,957 --> 00:14:37,043
Don't worry, he won't be
back again. - Thank you.

163
00:14:39,504 --> 00:14:41,214
Wow, almost...

164
00:14:42,674 --> 00:14:44,175
Aim it higher...

165
00:14:47,470 --> 00:14:48,888
You did it, Morad.

166
00:14:49,139 --> 00:14:51,016
You're the champ.

167
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:53,018
It's caught fire!

168
00:14:53,852 --> 00:14:57,147
Morad. Here's Aaron.
Ask him about the clothes.

169
00:15:00,734 --> 00:15:02,318
Playing with fire?

170
00:15:03,528 --> 00:15:05,113
Aaron, how are my clothes?

171
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,242
The trousers are all right,
but the shirt...

172
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:11,327
Come later,
I've got a shirt for you.

173
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:13,329
What happened
to your hair?

174
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:15,874
Yisrael's got it.
- Playing cards?

175
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:20,253
I'll get it back but...
- Natural looks best.

176
00:15:21,296 --> 00:15:23,798
Don't block the passage.

177
00:15:25,342 --> 00:15:27,052
Let me try once.

178
00:15:45,695 --> 00:15:50,116
Need any help?
- Hey, Aaron.

179
00:15:54,746 --> 00:15:56,581
You've grown stout.

180
00:15:57,123 --> 00:15:59,125
We're not children anymore.

181
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:05,215
How are you?

182
00:16:06,675 --> 00:16:08,259
All right.

183
00:16:11,388 --> 00:16:13,556
It's been 25 years.

184
00:16:16,851 --> 00:16:18,853
Gone in a flash.

185
00:16:21,815 --> 00:16:23,900
How did he die, Aaron?

186
00:16:25,110 --> 00:16:29,823
Merciful God, Morris's heart
gave way in his sleep.

187
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:32,325
He went to bed
and didn't get up again.

188
00:16:32,492 --> 00:16:35,078
Was he angry at me?

189
00:16:36,079 --> 00:16:40,583
Ever since you left
something inside of him died.

190
00:16:40,709 --> 00:16:42,210
He was never the same again.

191
00:16:50,343 --> 00:16:51,511
He loved you, Avram.

192
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:55,181
He missed you a lot.

193
00:16:59,144 --> 00:17:01,062
I made a mistake.

194
00:17:01,187 --> 00:17:03,982
I should have come back
to talk to him before he died.

195
00:17:09,821 --> 00:17:12,574
At least you'll say Kaddish
at the service.

196
00:17:17,412 --> 00:17:20,331
Yonatan, make sure
the potatoes don't burn.

197
00:17:21,499 --> 00:17:24,002
Don't worry, I'll manage.

198
00:17:24,169 --> 00:17:27,380
How long has Avram been gone?

199
00:17:28,131 --> 00:17:31,259
20, maybe 15 years,
I don't know exactly.

200
00:17:33,219 --> 00:17:36,222
Much more.
At least 30 years.

201
00:17:37,015 --> 00:17:39,726
He left the night Morris
and Seniora got married.

202
00:17:40,018 --> 00:17:43,646
Shoo away the smoke.
I remember that wedding.

203
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:46,733
People drowned in tears.

204
00:17:48,985 --> 00:17:50,904
Why did he leave?

205
00:17:51,696 --> 00:17:56,159
Why? He and Morris
argued over the theater.

206
00:17:58,620 --> 00:18:00,121
Go.

207
00:18:03,416 --> 00:18:04,626
What's he come back for?

208
00:18:05,418 --> 00:18:07,587
What for? To say Kaddish
for his brother.

209
00:18:08,171 --> 00:18:09,964
He's a year late.

210
00:18:18,431 --> 00:18:20,308
He asked about you.

211
00:18:20,642 --> 00:18:21,851
Your turn.

212
00:18:23,812 --> 00:18:26,272
Aren't you going
to talk to him?

213
00:18:29,818 --> 00:18:32,987
What's there to talk about?
- Life.

214
00:18:35,198 --> 00:18:36,533
Whose life?

215
00:19:43,224 --> 00:19:45,018
We'll use a large board.
- Yes.

216
00:19:45,143 --> 00:19:48,229
Here we install the crossbar
of the bicycle

217
00:19:48,355 --> 00:19:50,190
and these are the handlebars.

218
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:53,485
The white wheel goes here...

219
00:19:53,610 --> 00:19:57,155
One wheel over here,
and another over here.

220
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:59,616
What about axles?
- Axles?

221
00:19:59,824 --> 00:20:04,079
One plank here,
and another over here.

222
00:20:04,204 --> 00:20:06,498
How is it going to hold?
- Size 10 nails.

223
00:20:07,165 --> 00:20:11,961
We overturn this crate
and install it up here.

224
00:20:12,796 --> 00:20:17,342
It can carry lots of wood.
- A real jet wagon!

225
00:20:17,676 --> 00:20:21,429
I can't get that dream
about Dad out of my mind.

226
00:20:21,596 --> 00:20:24,391
That's because
of his memorial service.

227
00:20:24,557 --> 00:20:28,395
George, he wants us
to undo the vow.

228
00:20:28,603 --> 00:20:31,940
The place's been closed for
30 years. It's all in ruins.

229
00:20:32,315 --> 00:20:33,441
So what?

230
00:20:33,566 --> 00:20:35,443
We can get it
organized in a jiffy.

231
00:20:39,239 --> 00:20:41,032
Hi there.

232
00:20:41,783 --> 00:20:44,828
What are you up to,
building a spaceship?

233
00:20:44,953 --> 00:20:47,622
We'll use it
to carry the lumber.

234
00:20:47,789 --> 00:20:50,417
A lumber shuttle to
clear the entire neighborhood.

235
00:20:51,418 --> 00:20:52,460
What are you doing?

236
00:20:52,752 --> 00:20:56,047
I've been trying to open it
for half an hour!

237
00:20:56,172 --> 00:20:59,509
Try the other way around.
- I knew it!

238
00:21:02,887 --> 00:21:05,640
Any coffee?
- It's on its way.

239
00:21:18,862 --> 00:21:20,113
Binyamin, how are you?

240
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:22,282
Okay, Mrs. Seniora. And you?

241
00:21:22,449 --> 00:21:25,452
Fine. How much is this?
- 5 shekels.

242
00:21:25,577 --> 00:21:28,204
And the apples?
- 6 shekels.

243
00:21:28,329 --> 00:21:30,915
Need anything else?
- No.

244
00:21:34,961 --> 00:21:37,339
Weigh them for me, please.

245
00:21:51,019 --> 00:21:52,812
Hello, Seniora.

246
00:21:54,898 --> 00:21:56,900
Weigh them, please.

247
00:22:13,083 --> 00:22:15,293
Look at this.
- Great.

248
00:22:15,585 --> 00:22:17,504
Now take it apart.

249
00:22:17,629 --> 00:22:19,881
We need the fork.
- Alright.

250
00:22:20,382 --> 00:22:23,051
Come on, Morad,
do your Tarzan bit.

251
00:22:23,176 --> 00:22:25,762
Lay off it, George,
we've got a wagon to build.

252
00:22:26,096 --> 00:22:28,682
Come on. You haven't
done it in a long while.

253
00:22:29,724 --> 00:22:31,101
Just once for the gang.

254
00:22:31,434 --> 00:22:32,602
Go for it.

255
00:22:34,938 --> 00:22:36,690
You guys are something...

256
