00:44:17,615 --> 00:44:19,075
Meanwhile, he pulls out
a bottle of whiskey

505
00:44:19,200 --> 00:44:22,579
and gulps down a few sips.
A few minutes later

506
00:44:26,458 --> 00:44:29,586
Fernando Sancho shows up
with 50 or 60 roughnecks,

507
00:44:29,711 --> 00:44:32,630
each one uglier than the next.

508
00:44:32,881 --> 00:44:34,841
They get off their horses.

509
00:44:34,966 --> 00:44:36,885
Jango takes his time.

510
00:44:37,010 --> 00:44:40,972
He tosses away the bottle and
strips the blanket from the gun,

511
00:44:41,097 --> 00:44:43,808
grips the hand-crank and...

512
00:44:46,394 --> 00:44:49,731
In just seconds he mows down
the entire band of Mexicans.

513
00:44:49,856 --> 00:44:52,192
Some of them fall this way,
others fall that way.

514
00:44:53,151 --> 00:44:56,196
So he killed all of them?
- Rubbed them out completely.

515
00:44:56,404 --> 00:44:59,032
He plugged them full of holes

516
00:44:59,491 --> 00:45:01,910
so the tequila poured
out of them.

517
00:45:02,577 --> 00:45:05,580
In short, the Mexicans
came looking for gold

518
00:45:06,414 --> 00:45:08,333
and got hot lead instead.

519
00:45:09,417 --> 00:45:11,169
They made great movies
in the old days...

520
00:45:11,711 --> 00:45:14,881
Yonatan, who's stronger,
Hercules or Machista? - Machista.

521
00:45:15,006 --> 00:45:16,716
Are you kidding?
Hercules is stronger.

522
00:45:16,841 --> 00:45:18,927
No way, Machista is stronger.

523
00:45:19,052 --> 00:45:21,388
Aaron, who's stronger,
Machista or Hercules?

524
00:45:21,513 --> 00:45:24,516
Machista is no competition,
Hercules was much stronger.

525
00:45:24,891 --> 00:45:26,351
What did I tell you?

526
00:45:28,520 --> 00:45:32,232
So, do we have a projector?
- You bet.

527
00:45:32,565 --> 00:45:33,817
How about the movie?

528
00:45:34,567 --> 00:45:39,614
The movie? The dealer says that of
all the movies he bought from Dad

529
00:45:39,948 --> 00:45:42,701
only "Sangam" is missing.
- Where could it be?

530
00:45:45,328 --> 00:45:47,414
Only your uncle could have it.

531
00:45:48,540 --> 00:45:50,417
But wait and I'll find out.

532
00:46:03,638 --> 00:46:04,639
Hey, Avram.

533
00:46:05,849 --> 00:46:08,018
How's it going?
- Alright.

534
00:46:11,104 --> 00:46:14,149
Tell me, have you got "Sangam"?

535
00:46:14,941 --> 00:46:15,942
What?

536
00:46:16,067 --> 00:46:18,486
The movie "Sangam,"
haven't you got it?

537
00:46:20,321 --> 00:46:21,865
What do you want?

538
00:46:21,990 --> 00:46:24,451
We want to screen it
in the movie theater.

539
00:46:26,578 --> 00:46:28,621
No movie, Aaron.

540
00:46:30,206 --> 00:46:32,584
The dealer says that of all the
movies he bought,

541
00:46:32,709 --> 00:46:35,337
only "Sangam" is missing.
So where could it be?

542
00:46:36,087 --> 00:46:37,714
Only you could have it.

543
00:46:40,133 --> 00:46:44,304
Tell me, is Seniora behind it all?

544
00:46:44,429 --> 00:46:46,931
Enough, Avram,
don't be stubborn.

545
00:46:47,349 --> 00:46:50,018
Come see how we've put
new chairs in the theater,

546
00:46:50,185 --> 00:46:52,354
a new screen and projector.

547
00:46:55,106 --> 00:46:58,360
Come on, let's relive
our old dreams.

548
00:47:00,987 --> 00:47:02,489
The past is dead.

549
00:47:04,157 --> 00:47:06,242
It's dead.

550
00:47:40,318 --> 00:47:45,115
Raise it a little more.
Some more. That's it.

551
00:47:46,408 --> 00:47:49,661
Watch out, Morad,
you'll burn down the theater!

552
00:47:49,828 --> 00:47:51,121
Are you mad?

553
00:48:11,641 --> 00:48:13,143
Bored?

554
00:48:13,977 --> 00:48:16,354
Why do you think I'm bored?

555
00:48:18,314 --> 00:48:21,484
Watch my little girl, I'm going
to get her something to drink.

556
00:48:32,954 --> 00:48:35,582
How are you, Amalya?
- Alright.

557
00:48:37,584 --> 00:48:39,044
Look at me.

558
00:48:42,881 --> 00:48:46,134
How do I look?
- Handsome.

559
00:48:47,802 --> 00:48:50,472
What does your mom say
about me? - Cute.

560
00:48:52,057 --> 00:48:54,642
Cute means imbecile.
- That's right.

561
00:48:56,686 --> 00:48:59,606
Won't you put in a word for me?
- Do it yourself.

562
00:49:00,273 --> 00:49:01,649
You're just like your mom.

563
00:49:01,775 --> 00:49:04,402
He'll spoil your girl.
- Don't interfere.

564
00:49:06,571 --> 00:49:10,075
Why are you mixing her up?
- This is serious conversation!

565
00:49:10,200 --> 00:49:12,452
Playing the bogey man...

566
00:49:13,495 --> 00:49:15,497
I heard there's a new singer.

567
00:49:15,622 --> 00:49:18,083
No, she only sings
in the shower.

568
00:49:18,208 --> 00:49:20,460
I bet you'd love
to do backing vocals.

569
00:49:20,669 --> 00:49:22,128
Did I say anything?

570
00:49:22,462 --> 00:49:25,256
No, you're a real silent movie.

571
00:49:26,049 --> 00:49:27,050
Come on, honey.

572
00:49:42,399 --> 00:49:44,401
Got the hots?

573
00:49:46,820 --> 00:49:47,987
I'm burning!

574
00:49:52,075 --> 00:49:53,368
Now it's my turn.

575
00:49:53,493 --> 00:49:56,454
Sarah, I'm in a big hurry.
I don't want to play anymore.

576
00:49:56,579 --> 00:49:59,165
Sarah, it'll be easier
to hit him from here.

577
00:50:00,333 --> 00:50:03,586
Sarah, I've got things to do.

578
00:50:06,840 --> 00:50:09,259
Morad, you said that
we'd change places.

579
00:50:10,677 --> 00:50:13,471
You promised, Morad.
I don't want to play anymore.

580
00:50:13,596 --> 00:50:15,682
Enough, Morad!

581
00:50:19,352 --> 00:50:22,105
Morad, I swear that I'll
give her back the stocking!

582
00:50:30,572 --> 00:50:32,490
Release him right away.

583
00:50:32,615 --> 00:50:35,285
We were just fooling with him.
- Stop fooling with him.

584
00:50:35,410 --> 00:50:40,331
Nissim, he asked for it.
- Okay, clear out of here.

585
00:50:40,457 --> 00:50:44,002
Nissim, I want him to give back
my stocking and my cassettes.

586
00:50:44,419 --> 00:50:47,339
Alright, move it.
Clear out of here.

587
00:50:50,592 --> 00:50:54,220
7 against 1? Shame on you.
- You shut up!

588
00:50:54,554 --> 00:50:56,097
Come here.

589
00:50:57,932 --> 00:51:00,935
Come over here!

590
00:51:17,327 --> 00:51:18,328
What's this?

591
00:51:19,162 --> 00:51:20,997
It's Sarah's.

592
00:51:21,456 --> 00:51:23,375
This is Sarah's?

593
00:51:25,418 --> 00:51:28,588
You had everyone alarmed,
we were sure it was real.

594
00:51:30,298 --> 00:51:33,176
Go on, take it apart and
return the stocking to her.

595
00:51:33,760 --> 00:51:36,221
Go on,
return it to her!

596
00:52:05,750 --> 00:52:07,919
Don't like resistance,
do you?

597
00:52:09,129 --> 00:52:10,922
It runs in the family.

598
00:52:28,815 --> 00:52:30,483
Aren't you going to sing?

599
00:55:08,183 --> 00:55:11,478
We'll pay him,
how much does he want?

600
00:55:13,480 --> 00:55:15,857
It's not a matter
of money, Nissim.

601
00:55:16,107 --> 00:55:20,612
So what's the problem?
What does he want?

602
00:55:23,531 --> 00:55:25,825
You can't give him
what he wants.

603
00:55:27,660 --> 00:55:31,664
I could get it in a cinch.
You pay him too much respect.

604
00:55:34,292 --> 00:55:37,295
Be patient, Nissim.

605
00:55:52,352 --> 00:55:53,353
Yisrael.

606
00:55:55,897 --> 00:55:58,983
Is it holding in the wind?
- Like concrete.

607
00:55:59,109 --> 00:56:01,111
If it doesn't hold,
use thumbtacks.

608
00:56:02,070 --> 00:56:04,322
Have you got the jitters?
- Have I got the jitters?

609
00:56:04,447 --> 00:56:06,658
My stomach is churning,
I'm counting the minutes.

610
00:56:07,325 --> 00:56:08,993
Come here, sit down.

611
00:56:19,546 --> 00:56:21,840
Now you won't have
to climb on the roof.

612
00:56:24,467 --> 00:56:26,761
Now you'll have a ticket.

613
00:56:27,679 --> 00:56:31,433
Yeah, but it'd better be
a good seat in the middle.

614
00:56:31,850 --> 00:56:34,769
Yisrael, how many times
have you seen "Sangam"?

615
00:56:35,228 --> 00:56:38,023
A 100 maybe 200 times.

616
00:56:39,107 --> 00:56:41,234
From the matinee show
until 4 in the morning.

617
00:56:41,359 --> 00:56:43,820
Why do you always
exaggerate?

618
00:56:44,195 --> 00:56:46,239
No exaggeration, I swear.

619
00:56:46,573 --> 00:56:48,283
First, the matinee show...

620
00:56:48,491 --> 00:56:49,868
then the evening show...

621
00:56:49,993 --> 00:56:52,704
and the late night show
with Avram and Seniora.

622
00:57:00,003 --> 00:57:01,463
I swear.

623
00:57:03,006 --> 00:57:05,425
I'd peek from the roof.

624
00:57:05,925 --> 00:57:09,554
What an amazing view.
- Which roof?

625
00:57:10,263 --> 00:57:12,432
The roof of the theater.

626
00:57:12,557 --> 00:57:15,560
You saw Avram and Seniora
from the roof?

627
00:57:15,685 --> 00:57:18,772
They used to watch "Sangam."
- Did you ever tell anyone?

628
00:57:20,940 --> 00:57:23,234
No, I swear.

629
00:57:24,444 --> 00:57:25,445
Yisrael.

630
00:57:31,242 --> 00:57:33,286
Don't speak like that
about Seniora

631
00:57:33,411 --> 00:57:36,498
because it could make
the wrong impression.

632
00:57:37,457 --> 00:57:39,751
I won't say anything.

633
00:57:41,753 --> 00:57:44,130
Go on inside.

634
00:58:02,315 --> 00:58:04,401
Is that the truth
or is he making it up?

635
00:58:08,279 --> 00:58:10,865
You think Dad shut down
the theater without a reason?

636
00:58:14,869 --> 00:58:15,870
So?

637
00:58:16,871 --> 00:58:19,332
Do you mean to tell me that
Mom was involved with Avram?

638
00:58:19,833 --> 00:58:21,918
I really don't know.

639
00:58:31,302 --> 00:58:34,431
For the eternal soul of Morris,
the son of Rebecca Mandebon.

640
00:58:34,764 --> 00:58:37,684
May the spirit of the Lord
be his guide to Paradise.

641
00:58:42,731 --> 00:58:43,732
Amen!

642
00:58:44,649 --> 00:58:47,193
Amen.
- Amen.

643
00:58:50,321 --> 00:58:52,157
What's the matter with you?

644
00:58:53,158 --> 00:58:55,493
Everything's alright, Mom.

645
00:58:56,828 --> 00:58:59,706
We're going to the synagogue
to check if everything's ready.

646
00:59:06,338 --> 00:59:08,340
Get up already.

647
00:59:09,466 --> 00:59:11,593
Go on, get up!

648
00:59:14,262 --> 00:59:16,681
Go straight!

649
00:59:18,933 --> 00:59:21,186
What do you thing you're doing?

650
00:59:22,937 --> 00:59:25,315
That's it.
You can park here.

651
00:59:27,233 --> 00:59:28,610
Come on, Morad.

652
00:59:28,735 --> 00:59:31,488
Look how much wood Yisrael's got!

653
00:59:34,783 --> 00:59:37,285
Did I split my skull?
- No, just a tiny bump.

654
00:59:37,410 --> 00:59:40,205
Damn this board!
- What's the problem?

655
00:59:40,330 --> 00:59:42,999
This board is the problem!
- Let's take it to the bonfire.

656
00:59:43,124 --> 00:59:44,793
It's good for the bonfire!

657
00:59:44,959 --> 00:59:48,797
Pull, pull hard.
It's no good this way.

658
00:59:49,130 --> 00:59:53,176
Come over here.
- No, I'll go there.

659
00:59:54,260 --> 00:59:56,513
All together now:

660
00:59:56,638 --> 00:59:58,723
One, two, three, pull...

661
01:00:02,268 --> 01:00:04,646
Oh no, look what we've done!

662
01:00:04,771 --> 01:00:07,774
Now he'll be able to get
the motorcycle inside.

663
01:00:07,899 --> 01:00:09,943
We've made him a garage.

664
01:00:11,528 --> 01:00:12,696
Come on, let's take the boards.

665
01:00:18,076 --> 01:00:21,579
Dear Morris,
God bless his soul.

666
01:00:28,795 --> 01:00:29,796
Seniora.

667
01:00:30,797 --> 01:00:33,383
Life is a flowing river and
we're not getting any younger.

668
01:00:33,508 --> 01:00:36,386
Whatever is left unresolved
will remain that way forever.

669
01:00:37,345 --> 01:00:40,849
You should talk to him.

670
01:00:41,182 --> 01:00:43,435
I'm not going to talk to him.

671
01:00:43,560 --> 01:00:45,395
It'll turn out badly,
I'm telling you.

672
01:00:46,271 --> 01:00:48,314
Nissim is furious.

673
01:00:51,735 --> 01:00:53,778
You're the only one
he'll give the movie to.

674
01:00:53,903 --> 01:00:56,406
They can screen
a different movie.

675
01:00:56,531 --> 01:00:58,658
There's no point now
in opening old wounds.

676
01:00:58,783 --> 01:01:00,660
Will there ever be
an end to the story?

677
01:01:00,785 --> 01:01:02,537
It ended long ago.

678
01:01:03,538 --> 01:01:05,290
Know when, Aaron?

679
01:01:05,582 --> 01:01:08,752
That night when I waited
for him beside the theater.

680
01:01:09,210 --> 01:01:12,547
"I'll just go talk to Morris,
I'll be right back," he said.

681
01:01:14,674 --> 01:01:17,010
I waited all night.
Until morning.

682
01:01:17,886 --> 01:01:20,138
Until the sun rose.

683
01:01:22,223 --> 01:01:24,017
That's when it ended.

684
01:01:31,441 --> 01:01:34,527
Be careful.
- Move aside.

685
01:01:38,990 --> 01:01:41,326
You're a whale, damn you!

686
01:01:41,659 --> 01:01:43,995
Enough, Morad,
or I'll drown you.

687
01:02:05,892 --> 01:02:08,895
Yisrael, come in! What are
you afraid of? Come on!

688
01:03:58,797 --> 01:04:00,674
What's he doing here?

689
01:04:15,188 --> 01:04:18,692
Why has he come now? He didn't
bother to come to the funeral.

690
01:04:18,817 --> 01:04:22,445
Let him be.
- Why should I?

691
01:04:22,696 --> 01:04:24,948
He's won't give the movie
yet has the nerve to come here!

692
01:04:25,073 --> 01:04:27,117
Enough, Nissim, not now.

693
01:04:51,975 --> 01:04:54,102
The sons of the deceased
will say Kaddish.

694
01:04:55,145 --> 01:04:57,480
His brother too.
- He's not saying Kaddish for Dad!

695
01:04:57,647 --> 01:04:59,524
Calm down, Nissim,
he's his brother.

696
01:04:59,649 --> 01:05:02,152
He's not saying Kaddish
for Morris Mandebon.

697
01:05:03,653 --> 01:05:05,447
Not for Dad.

698
01:05:43,818 --> 01:05:45,362
What's the matter with you?

699
01:05:45,487 --> 01:05:47,030
He came to say Kaddish
for his brother

700
01:05:47,155 --> 01:05:48,698
and you go crazy on him?

701
01:05:48,823 --> 01:05:50,158
In the synagogue,
for all to see?

702
01:05:50,283 --> 01:05:53,286
You think I don't know why
Dad shut down the theater?

703
01:05:55,413 --> 01:05:57,832
Aaron.
- What?

704
01:05:58,917 --> 01:06:00,960
Tell us what went on there.

705
01:06:01,086 --> 01:06:02,337
What do you mean?

706
01:06:03,838 --> 01:06:07,175
You screened it for them.
- Yisrael told us all about it.

707
01:06:08,176 --> 01:06:09,177
It's true.

708
01:06:09,427 --> 01:06:11,888
I screened "Sangam" for them
when everyone had gone.

709
01:06:12,013 --> 01:06:15,558
So, was Avram
in love with Mom?

710
01:06:16,059 --> 01:06:18,353
Everybody was.

711
01:06:19,437 --> 01:06:21,564
But as for her, she had
her heart set on Avram.

712
01:06:21,690 --> 01:06:23,733
Did Dad know about it?

713
01:06:24,609 --> 01:06:27,529
If he'd known, he would
have stayed away from her.

714
01:06:28,530 --> 01:06:32,117
But the parents arranged a match
and it put Avram in a terrible jam.

715
01:06:32,534 --> 01:06:35,078
His only way out
was to disappear.

716
01:06:35,370 --> 01:06:37,205
That's why he won't give us
the movie?

717
01:06:37,330 --> 01:06:40,208
George, it's not just
any movie.

718
01:06:40,667 --> 01:06:42,836
"Sangam" was their movie.

719
01:07:18,663 --> 01:07:21,499
"De-Gaulle"

720
01:07:23,626 --> 01:07:25,837
Morad, straighten out the doll.

721
01:07:29,758 --> 01:07:33,178
Watch out for nails, Baruch,
or you'll hurt yourself.

722
01:07:34,262 --> 01:07:37,098
We have to reinforce it, Yonatan.

723
01:07:37,557 --> 01:07:40,352
There won't be any "Sangam."
- Why? Too bad.

724
01:07:40,643 --> 01:07:43,730
There's no "Sangam"?
- Avram won't let them have it.

725
01:07:44,481 --> 01:07:46,024
What a pity.

726
01:07:46,149 --> 01:07:48,943
I saw the movie with my mother
30 years ago.

727
01:07:49,069 --> 01:07:51,529
Everyone cried.
It was so much fun.

728
01:07:51,654 --> 01:07:53,490
I really wanted to see it.

729
01:07:53,615 --> 01:07:56,701
Badriya told me about the
movie for 3 hours, crying,

730
01:07:57,077 --> 01:07:59,829
and she said it was nothing
compared to the movie itself.

731
01:08:31,986 --> 01:08:32,987
Seniora.

732
01:08:52,257 --> 01:08:54,342
Why did you come here?

733
01:08:55,969 --> 01:08:58,054
To talk to you.

734
01:09:03,727 --> 01:09:06,688
Not a day passed that
I didn't think of you.

735
01:09:16,656 --> 01:09:18,616
Thought of me?

736
01:09:19,617 --> 01:09:22,412
So why didn't you
talk to Morris?

737
01:09:22,662 --> 01:09:25,165
You promised
you'd tell him about us.

738
01:09:25,832 --> 01:09:28,293
I didn't have the courage.

739
01:09:29,586 --> 01:09:32,005
He was so happy.

740
01:09:32,964 --> 01:09:36,634
When I came to talk to him, he
asked me to be his best man.

741
01:09:37,052 --> 01:09:39,846
The words stuck in my throat,
I couldn't speak a word.

742
01:09:40,930 --> 01:09:42,891
So you ran away?

743
01:09:43,099 --> 01:09:47,145
Had I stayed, it'd be like
living in a cage all my life.

744
01:09:48,313 --> 01:09:50,106
I had to go.

745
01:09:51,983 --> 01:09:54,694
Had you talked to him,
he would have understood.

746
01:09:59,616 --> 01:10:01,701
I made a mistake, Seniora.

747
01:10:04,496 --> 01:10:07,082
Now there's nobody
to talk to anymore.

748
01:10:08,124 --> 01:10:10,418
What used to be
can never be again.

749
01:10:15,757 --> 01:10:16,758
Seniora.

750
01:10:48,665 --> 01:10:53,753
"Morris Mandebon - R.I.P."

751
01:10:55,296 --> 01:10:58,550
You'll blast us to the sky
with your bonfire.

752
01:10:58,925 --> 01:11:01,720
We'll light the bonfire when
everyone leaves the theater.

753
01:11:02,053 --> 01:11:04,472
It'll be just like fireworks.

754
01:11:10,729 --> 01:11:11,730
Hey, Avram?

755
01:11:13,106 --> 01:11:16,151
Come have coffee with us.
- Some other time.

756
01:11:21,740 --> 01:11:23,700
Come and get "Sangam."

757
01:11:25,160 --> 01:11:26,161
Right on!

758
01:11:29,372 --> 01:11:31,791
I'll send Yisrael to pick
it up on his motorcycle.

759
01:11:32,792 --> 01:11:34,669
Come see the movie.

760
01:11:35,420 --> 01:11:38,131
I'll save you a seat, Avram.

761
01:11:48,308 --> 01:11:53,646
"Sangam"

762
01:12:47,075 --> 01:12:51,246
Morad, put these fuel tanks inside.
Hide them well.

763
01:12:53,581 --> 01:12:56,626
Morad! Look, it's leaking.

764
01:12:57,919 --> 01:12:59,838
Bring it over here.

765
01:13:00,296 --> 01:13:01,673
Plug it with this.

766
01:13:03,466 --> 01:13:05,969
Wait a minute.
I have a better idea.

767
01:13:07,345 --> 01:13:09,931
You and your gizmos.

768
01:13:10,807 --> 01:13:12,559
I hope this works.

769
01:13:12,684 --> 01:13:13,685
Good for you.

770
01:13:13,810 --> 01:13:15,687
Morad, put it inside

771
01:13:16,479 --> 01:13:17,772
so nobody will find it.

772
01:13:23,820 --> 01:13:25,822
Put the board back
so nobody can see it.

773
01:13:31,911 --> 01:13:34,122
Bet you it's going to be
the biggest bonfire ever.

774
01:13:34,247 --> 01:13:36,458
We worked hard, didn't we?

775
01:13:36,583 --> 01:13:38,793
Who'll guard the bonfire?

776
01:13:39,711 --> 01:13:41,546
How should I know?

777
01:13:41,713 --> 01:13:43,590
We'll post Jellyfish David.

778
01:13:44,174 --> 01:13:46,301
We'll be watching the movie.

779
01:13:46,551 --> 01:13:48,928
Okay, Jellyfish David,
he'll be the guard.
